sudo su - hdfs
List:
hadoop fs -ls
Create Dir:
hadoop fs -mkdir <dir name>
Change Ownership:
hadoop fs -chown <dir name/ file name>
Put:
hadoop fs -put <file name> <Path>
Cat:
hdfs dfs -cat file:///file /user/hadoop/file
hadoop fs -D dfs.blocksize=2m -put <> <>
Find:
find /hadoop/hdfs/ -name '<blkname*>'
From Local:
hdfs dfs -copyFromLocal <localsrc> URI
Count:
hdfs dfs -count [-q] <paths>
Copy:
hdfs dfs -cp /user/hadoop/file1 /user/hadoop/file2
Get:
hdfs dfs -get /user/hadoop/file localfile
Move:
hdfs dfs -mv /user/hadoop/file1 /user/hadoop/file2
Similar: rm, tail etc.
